cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.IR. 

This paper deals with natural language processing and specifically focuses on sequence to sequence models for sentence simplification. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the use of neural networks and pre-trained word embeddings, which are common in machine learning (cs.LG and cs.AI). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of a novel loss function and word-copy mechanism, which could fall under the categories of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval), respectively.
